Code:
---------------------------------------
All source code is stored in ClearCase in the WEB_TOOLS vobs. 
	---------------------------------------
	Environment Setup:
	---------------------------------------
	Development will all be done on chi1pbs1 using your personal login (md1....).  A one-time enviornment setup is needed.
	1) login to chi1bldX (1,2,3) as md1xxxx1
        2) Add the following lines to bottom of .cshrc file
		if ( "$HOST" == "chi1pbs1" ) then
		    setenv ENV '.kshrc'
		    ksh
		endif
	3) cp ~md1csta1/.kshrc $HOME
	4) cp ~md1csta1/.infranet_profile .
	5) cp ~md1csta1/.infranet_aliases .

	---------------------------------------
	DEVELOPMENT:
	---------------------------------------

	---------------------------------------
	UNIX 
	---------------------------------------
	1) login to chi1pbs1 with personal login (md1xxxx1 or chi1xxxx1)
	2) Create a clearcase view (cleartool mkview -tag <view-tag> -stgloc usc_viewstg where <view-tag> is the name of the view.)
	3) ct setview view-tag (created in previous step)       
	3) cd /vobs/web_tools/web

	---------------------------------------
	Eclipse 
	---------------------------------------
        1) Install Eclipse and ClearCase Plugin (if not already done)
	2) Mount the VOB:
		Click ClearCase - Mount VOB
		Choose web_tools (Reconnect at Logon should be checked)
	3) Create Java Project
		File - New - Project - Java Project 
		Choose name and location (ie: calldump and location ie: c:\workspace) 
	4) Create View
		ClearCase - Create New View
		Next - Snapshot - Location (ie: c:\workspace\LOCATION in previous step)


---------------------------------------
Build:
---------------------------------------
prod: ant -propertyfile conf/calldump.properties war		(produces calldump.war)
test: ant -propertyfile conf/calldump_test.properties war	(produces calldump_test.war)

---------------------------------------
Unit Testing:
---------------------------------------

	---------------------------------------
	UNIX 
	---------------------------------------
	ant -propertyfile test/env/unittest.properties rununittest <enter> 

	---------------------------------------
	Eclipse 
	---------------------------------------
        1) Window - Show View - Ant
	2) Configure Runtime 
		Run - External Tools - External Tools
		Find build.xml for project 
		in "Arguments" specify: -propertyfile test/env/unittest.properties rununittest
	3) Close out
	4) In Ant View - Click "rununittest" and hit RUN button
		

